</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[125,1172,1596,1685]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1032">
Body length 217 
<emphasis box="[319,334,1596,1620]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1032">M</emphasis>
m, colourless, cuticle smooth without pearls; eyes seem to be absent. The specimens were mounted in polyvinyl lactophenol more than 30 years ago, and no specification about the presence of eyes is indicated on the label.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5214262" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5214262" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5214262/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033" startId="6.[138,198,1014,1033]" targetBox="[380,943,135,976]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph blockId="6.[138,1185,1014,1060]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">
Figure 2. 
<taxonomicName authority="Pilato &amp; Binda &amp; Bertolani &amp; Lisi, 2005" authorityName="Pilato &amp; Binda &amp; Bertolani &amp; Lisi" authorityYear="2005" box="[236,462,1014,1033]" class="Eutardigrada" family="Hypsibiidae" genus="Diphascon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Parachela" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="serratum" status="sp. n." subGenus="Diphascon">
<emphasis box="[236,462,1014,1033]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">Diphascon (D.) serratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[470,525,1014,1033]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(A) Bucco-pharyngeal apparatus; (B) claws of the third pair of legs; (C) claws of the fourth pair of legs. Scale bar: 10 
<emphasis box="[602,614,1041,1060]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">M</emphasis>
m.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="6.[138,1185,1109,1685]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">
The bucco-pharyngeal apparatus is shown in 
<figureCitation box="[675,793,1109,1133]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[138,198,1014,1033]" captionTargetBox="[380,943,135,976]" captionTargetId="figure-315@6.[380,943,133,978]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Diphascon (D.) serratum sp. n. (A) Bucco-pharyngeal apparatus; (B) claws of the third pair of legs; (C) claws of the fourth pair of legs. Scale bar: 10 Mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5214262" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5214262/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">Figure 2A</figureCitation>
. The bucco-pharyngeal tube, measured from the anterior margin of the stylet sheaths to the base of the pharyngeal apophyses, is 49.9 
<emphasis box="[193,207,1174,1198]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">M</emphasis>
m in length; the buccal tube, measured from the anterior margin of the stylet sheaths to the end of the drop-shaped thickening is 21.6 
<emphasis box="[595,609,1206,1230]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">M</emphasis>
m in length (
<emphasis box="[747,779,1206,1230]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">pbf</emphasis>
543.3) and 2.5 
<emphasis box="[953,967,1206,1230]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">M</emphasis>
m wide (
<emphasis box="[1062,1095,1206,1230]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">ptd</emphasis>
511.6). The stylet supports are inserted on the buccal tube at 67.2% of its length (
<emphasis box="[1006,1039,1239,1263]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">ptd</emphasis>
567.2). The pharyngeal bulb has apophyses, three rod-shaped macroplacoids and microplacoid; the septulum is absent. The entire placoid row is 18.5 
<emphasis box="[687,701,1304,1328]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">M</emphasis>
m in length (
<emphasis box="[840,873,1303,1327]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">ptd</emphasis>
585.6) including the microplacoid, 16.5 
<emphasis box="[288,302,1336,1360]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">M</emphasis>
m (
<emphasis box="[340,373,1336,1360]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">ptd</emphasis>
576.4) excluding it; the first macroplacoid is 4.9 
<emphasis box="[914,928,1336,1360]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">M</emphasis>
m long (
<emphasis box="[1021,1054,1336,1360]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">ptd</emphasis>
522.7), the second 4.6 
<emphasis box="[263,277,1368,1392]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">M</emphasis>
m (
<emphasis box="[317,350,1368,1392]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">ptd</emphasis>
521.3), the third 6.9 
<emphasis box="[589,603,1368,1392]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">M</emphasis>
m (
<emphasis box="[642,675,1368,1392]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">ptd</emphasis>
531.9), the microplacoid 1.8 
<emphasis box="[1006,1020,1368,1392]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">M</emphasis>
m (
<emphasis box="[1060,1093,1368,1392]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">ptd</emphasis>
58.3).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[138,1185,1109,1685]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">
The claws (
<figureCitation box="[300,458,1401,1425]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[138,198,1014,1033]" captionTargetBox="[380,943,135,976]" captionTargetId="figure-315@6.[380,943,133,978]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Diphascon (D.) serratum sp. n. (A) Bucco-pharyngeal apparatus; (B) claws of the third pair of legs; (C) claws of the fourth pair of legs. Scale bar: 10 Mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5214262" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5214262/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">Figure 2B, C</figureCitation>
) have wide branches and as a consequence they appear stout. The claws of the hind legs (particularly the posterior claws) have an enlarged basal portion medially and laterally prolonged in a cuticular thickening and basal spines (
<figureCitation box="[1043,1171,1466,1490]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[138,198,1014,1033]" captionTargetBox="[380,943,135,976]" captionTargetId="figure-315@6.[380,943,133,978]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Diphascon (D.) serratum sp. n. (A) Bucco-pharyngeal apparatus; (B) claws of the third pair of legs; (C) claws of the fourth pair of legs. Scale bar: 10 Mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5214262" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5214262/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">Figure 2C</figureCitation>
). Basal spines are also present on the external claws of the first three pairs of legs (the basal margin of the internal claws is smooth). Well-developed accessory points are present on the main branches of all claws. The internal claws are 6.4 
<emphasis box="[777,792,1563,1587]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">M</emphasis>
m long (
<emphasis box="[893,927,1563,1587]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">ptd</emphasis>
529.6) on the second and third pair of legs, the external claws of the same pairs of legs are 8.6 
<emphasis box="[1082,1097,1596,1620]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">M</emphasis>
m long (
<emphasis box="[148,182,1628,1652]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">ptd</emphasis>
539.8); on the hind legs the anterior claws are 7.3 
<emphasis box="[832,847,1628,1652]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">M</emphasis>
m long (
<emphasis box="[958,992,1628,1652]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">ptd</emphasis>
533.8) and the posterior claws 9.2 
<emphasis box="[363,378,1661,1685]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">M</emphasis>
m (
<emphasis box="[420,454,1660,1684]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1033">ptd</emphasis>
542.6).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[125,1173,136,257]" box="[152,1173,136,160]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1034">On the first three pairs of legs a cuticular bar is present near the base of the internal claws.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[125,1173,136,257]" box="[152,340,168,192]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1034">Eggs not found.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[125,1173,136,257]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1034">
The 
<typeStatus box="[208,307,201,225]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1034">paratype</typeStatus>
is similar to the 
<typeStatus box="[503,607,201,225]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1034">holotype</typeStatus>
; in 
<tableCitation box="[650,736,201,225]" captionStart="Table I" captionStartId="5.[125,179,145,164]" captionText="Table I. Length (in Mm) of some structures of D. nobilei Binda, 1969, D. serratum sp. n., D. nelsonae sp. n., D. platyungue sp. n., and D. hydrophilum sp. n." pageId="7" pageNumber="1034">Table I</tableCitation>
the dimensions of some structures of the 
<typeStatus box="[171,271,233,257]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1034">holotype</typeStatus>
and of the known 
<typeStatus box="[495,594,233,257]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1034">paratype</typeStatus>
are indicated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[125,238,313,337]" box="[125,238,313,337]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1034">
<emphasis box="[125,238,313,337]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1034">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[125,1030,361,385]" box="[125,1030,361,385]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1034">
The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pilato &amp; Binda &amp; Bertolani &amp; Lisi" authorityYear="2005" box="[254,348,361,384]" class="Eutardigrada" family="Hypsibiidae" genus="Diphascon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Parachela" pageId="7" pageNumber="1034" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="serratum">
<emphasis box="[254,348,361,384]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1034">serratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the indentation of the basal margin of the claws.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[125,220,441,465]" box="[125,220,441,465]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1034">
<emphasis box="[125,220,441,465]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1034">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[125,1172,489,641]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1034">
<taxonomicName authority="Pilato &amp; Binda &amp; Bertolani &amp; Lisi, 2005" authorityName="Pilato &amp; Binda &amp; Bertolani &amp; Lisi" authorityYear="2005" box="[125,341,489,513]" class="Eutardigrada" family="Hypsibiidae" genus="Diphascon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Parachela" pageId="7" pageNumber="1034" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="serratum" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[125,341,489,513]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1034">Diphascon serratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[351,415,489,513]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1034" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Binda" authorityYear="1969" box="[570,677,489,513]" class="Eutardigrada" family="Hypsibiidae" genus="Diphascon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Parachela" pageId="7" pageNumber="1034" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="nobilei">
<emphasis box="[570,677,489,513]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1034">D. nobilei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a longer bucco-pharyngeal tube with respect to the body length, stylet supports inserted on the buccal tube in a more caudal position (
<tableCitation box="[233,321,553,577]" captionStart="Table I" captionStartId="5.[125,179,145,164]" captionText="Table I. Length (in Mm) of some structures of D. nobilei Binda, 1969, D. serratum sp. n., D. nelsonae sp. n., D. platyungue sp. n., and D. hydrophilum sp. n." pageId="7" pageNumber="1034">Table I</tableCitation>
), longer placoids both with respect to the body size and to the buccal tube length (
<tableCitation box="[214,304,585,609]" captionStart="Table I" captionStartId="5.[125,179,145,164]" captionText="Table I. Length (in Mm) of some structures of D. nobilei Binda, 1969, D. serratum sp. n., D. nelsonae sp. n., D. platyungue sp. n., and D. hydrophilum sp. n." pageId="7" pageNumber="1034">Table I</tableCitation>
), shorter claws with less-evident basal spines (absent on the internal claws of the first three pairs of legs) (
<figureCitation box="[490,602,617,641]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[138,198,1638,1657]" captionTargetBox="[278,1048,737,1600]" captionTargetId="figure-133@4.[275,1049,737,1601]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Diphascon (D.) nobilei Binda, 1969. (A) Bucco-pharyngeal apparatus; (B) claws of the third pair of legs; (C) claws of the fourth pair of legs. Scale bar: 10 Mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5214260" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5214260/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="1034">Figures 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[619,637,617,641]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[138,198,1014,1033]" captionTargetBox="[380,943,135,976]" captionTargetId="figure-315@6.[380,943,133,978]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Diphascon (D.) serratum sp. n. (A) Bucco-pharyngeal apparatus; (B) claws of the third pair of legs; (C) claws of the fourth pair of legs. Scale bar: 10 Mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5214262" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5214262/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="1034">2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
